div.p:
To winde a ſhip, is to bring her head about, either with the boate, or with ſome oares out at her hawſe or ſterne-portes (if ſhe be a ſmall ſhip
                     •
                  ) The ſhip winds-up, that is when ſhe comes to ride by her Anchor: when they are under ſaile, they uſe to aske, how winds the ſhip, that is, upon what point of the Compaſſe doth ſhe lie with her head.
